# S03-T05: Target Tracking Overlay

## Objective
Build primitive frame-differencing motion detection with bounding boxes, lock-on indicator, and AI-style threat classification labels. WOW factor for vacancy.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `src/features/hud/tracking/TargetTracker.ts` consumes `ImageBitmap` frames, outputs `Target[]`.
- Algorithm: frame differencing on downsampled grayscale, connected-component grouping.
- Each target: `{ id, bbox, confidence, classification, distance, bearing }`.
- Overlay component draws bbox + labels (TGT-001, THREAT-LVL, INTERCEPT-Xs).
- Animated lock-on ring (pulsing) on selected target.
- Status text states: `ACQUIRING...`, `OPEN`, `TRACKING`.

## Steps
1. Implement frame-diff worker (S03-T09 will move to OffscreenCanvas).
2. Define `Target` type and `useTrackingStore` (Zustand).
3. Build `<TargetOverlay>` Canvas component.
4. Implement classification heuristic (size + persistence → label).

## Invariants
- Detection runs at most 10Hz (LOW priority).
- No real ML — purely heuristic for demo impact.
- Threat colors per UI_REGULATION (pink = critical lock).
